@tpkn It seems to be a typo according to the code below! To let us better determine the cause of the problem, would you mind providing your file? I will submit a PR as soon as possible. 
```javascript
if (this.map.sheetPr.model && this.map.sheetPr.model.outlineProperties) {
     // outlinePropertiesx
     properties.outlineProperties = this.map.sheetPr.model.outlinePropertiesx;
}
```

@tpkn See https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/master/README.md#worksheet-properties.

```javascript
const Excel = require('../../lib/exceljs.nodejs');

const workbook = new Excel.Workbook();
workbook.xlsx.readFile('./test.xlsx').then(function () {
  const worksheet = workbook.getWorksheet(1);
 // setting
  worksheet.properties.defaultRowHeight = 15;
  workbook.xlsx.writeFile('./target.xml').then(() => {
    console.log('ok_write')
  });
});
```

@tpkn  The error is caused because there is no ``sheetFormatPr`` tag, but there are other errors. I will come up with my solution and then need to ask the authors and members of excel.js for suggestions.

@Siemienik @guyonroche any thoughts?

## Problems and solutions
1. The target attribute of **workbook.xml.rels** is an absolute path issue.
> Solutions
```javascript
// workbook.xml 
// worksheet = model.worksheetHash[`xl/${rel.Target}`];
worksheet = model.worksheetHash[`xl/${rel.Target.replace(/^(\s|\/xl\/)+/, '')}`]; 
```
2. The **sheet1.xml** in the newly created file should have the ``sheetFormatPr`` tag and default attribute.
> Solutions
```javascript
// worksheet.-xform.js
// const properties = this.map.sheetFormatPr.model; 
const properties = this.map.sheetFormatPr.model || {}; 
if (this.map.sheetPr.model && this.map.sheetPr.model.outlineProperties) {
   properties.outlineProperties = this.map.sheetPr.model.outlineProperties;
}

// sheet-format-properties-xform.js
 const attributes = {
    // defaultRowHeight: model.defaultRowHeight
    defaultRowHeight: model.defaultRowHeight || 15,
};
```
3.  Error messag: ``Deleted record: Document subject (workbook) in xl / workbook.xml section``.
>Solutions
```javascript
// workbook-properties-xform.js
 render(xmlStream, model) {
    xmlStream.leafNode('workbookPr', {
      date1904: model.date1904 ? 1 : undefined,
      // defaultThemeVersion: 164011,
      defaultThemeVersion: 124226,
      filterPrivacy: 1,
   });
}
```
